  "articleSummary": "This article introduces pragmatic TypeScript type-design strategies to resolve the common trade-off between explicit readability and reusable, DRY interfaces. Targeted at developers modeling semi-structured API data and entities, it contrasts monolithic object types with fragmented named interfaces before detailing techniques like indexed access type derivation and mix-ins to maintain consistent, predictable schemas. The tone is analytical and tutorial-driven, framed around “guerrilla” tactics that prioritize agile, IDE-friendly solutions over traditional OOP or ERD conventions. By leveraging TypeScript’s advanced type system, the piece advocates for composable type hierarchies that minimize naming variances and streamline developer workflows.",
